description:
While Ellen White was living at her home residence, Elmshaven, she received many visions from God. Following these visions, she often wrote letters and books about what she had learnt. It was also whilst spending her final years in this house that Ellen White was able to spend many precious moments with her grandchildren. We see a woman who gave much counsel to the church at large and individuals, but also a loving and caring grandmother who balanced her work for the church and her family life in an exemplary manner.

To find out more information about Elmshaven, Ellen White and her grandchildren visit our website to read our extended article.
